# Team Rules

## Ownership

- Platform squad: `platform-*` repos
- Education squad: `education-*` repos
- Social squad: `social-*` repos
- Contract changes need platform squad review

## Code standards

- **Frontend repos:** TypeScript strict mode (Next.js)
- **Backend repos:** Python 3.12+, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, psycopg2, Alembic, ruff
- Follow `simple-code.mdc` — clarity over cleverness
- No secrets in git; use env vars and vault in prod
- All public APIs documented in OpenAPI (`platform-contracts`) before merge

## Testing

- Unit tests for business logic
- Integration tests for API routes
- E2E for critical user paths (login, subscribe, core product flow)
- testing-agent must pass before review-agent

## Reviews

- code-review agent is required on every feature PR
- Architect review required for `platform-contracts` major bumps
- Two human approvals for production deploys (team policy)

## Communication

- Boundary changes → ADR in `docs/adr/`
- Breaking API changes → `#platform-contracts` channel + semver major

## Simplicity pledge

> Make the code so simple a human can read it like plain English. Do not write so many lines of code.

This applies to all squads. Refactor agent may be invoked when PRs exceed 400 lines.
